Package: howtheyvoteR
Title: Access and Cache the Latest Data Releases from HowTheyVote
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Maintainer: Paul Bochtler <paulbochtler.gh@gmail.com>
Authors@R: c(
  person("Paul", "Bochtler", 
         email = "paulbochtler.gh@gmail.com", 
         role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
         comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-9146-6185")))
Description: Provides utilities to programmatically download and cache
  release assets from the GitHub repository 'HowTheyVote/data'. Uses
  the 'piggyback' and 'gh' packages to interact with GitHub and caches
  downloaded data using 'memoise' and 'cachem' following R user cache
  directory conventions.
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports:
    piggyback,
    gh,
    tools,
    rlang,
    jsonlite,
    purrr,
    tibble,
    readr
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
